^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-16 13:12] observe — the HTML pages already share a strong structural skeleton, but many routes still omit the same top-level affordances: skip links, `main#main-content`, and stable section labels.
 >>[2026-04-16 13:18] observe — the heaviest repeated metadata (`seed`, `related-routes`, `context-relevance`, `promptability`, `collectability`, `locality`, `consequence`) is often hand-authored even though `spw-page-metadata.js` can infer much of it when missing.
 >>[2026-04-16 13:23] observe — CSS and JS mostly depend on a smaller core contract: `kind`, `role`, `surface`, `context`, `wonder`, `category-family`, `form`, and a few interaction-specific attributes.
 >>[2026-04-16 13:26] decide — sequence the pass as static HTML landmark normalization first, then runtime inference for repeated ids/ARIA relationships and metadata defaults, then a small CSS simplification for semantic display rules.
 >>[2026-04-16 13:28] hygiene — base ref recorded as main@9511b53; preserve the existing uncommitted settings/resonance follow-up and avoid unrelated runtime/css drift unless the semantic cleanup directly overlaps it.
 >>[2026-04-16 13:30] taste — the goal is not to strip the site down to generic HTML, but to make the semantic language feel intentional instead of over-serialized.
 >>[2026-04-16 14:01] implement — added skip links plus stable `main#main-content` targets across the public HTML routes, then labeled each main landmark from its visible page heading so the top-level reading order is explicit even before runtime enhancement.
 >>[2026-04-16 14:08] implement — `spw-page-metadata.js` now derives region heading ids, `aria-labelledby` links, `role="group"` for anonymous card/panel divs, and a reduced `role-cluster` contract so authored pages do not need to restate family semantics everywhere.
 >>[2026-04-16 14:16] implement — moved repeated role-family selector groups in `spw-handles.css`, `spw-grammar.css`, and `spw-ornament.css` onto `data-spw-role-cluster`, making the runtime the canonical translator from detailed role names to style families.
 >>[2026-04-16 14:22] implement — `site-settings.js` now primes declarative setting triggers with button semantics, keyboard activation, and shared active-state wiring while the root apply path uses grouped dataset/style helpers instead of a long run of one-off assignments.
 >>[2026-04-16 14:25] validate — `git diff --check`, `node --check public/js/site-settings.js`, `node --check public/js/spw-page-metadata.js`, and audits for skip links plus `main[aria-labelledby]` all passed.
}

